# Connect Frontend and Backend

This plan connects the existing React+Vite frontend with the Django production backend to create a seamlessly integrated full-stack application.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The workspace currently contains a **Vite + React** app (`smart-shop-compare-f419ce5b`) rather than a **Next.js** app. I will proceed with configuring this Vite app (using `VITE_` env vars instead of `NEXT_PUBLIC_`) to properly link with Django. If this is not the intended frontend folder, please let me know. 

> [!NOTE]
> To securely store JWT tokens, I will configure Django to issue them as `HttpOnly` cookies via `dj_rest_auth`, and add `JWTCookieAuthentication` to the backend. The frontend API client already uses `credentials: 'include'`, which securely transmits these token cookies on all requests without manually setting an `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header in JavaScript.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Configuration (thabuyer_backend)

#### [MODIFY] `core/settings.py`
- Update `ALLOWED_HOSTS` to fallback accurately.
- Update `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` to permit `http://localhost:3000`, `http://127.0.0.1:3000`, and `https://thabuyer.vercel.app`.
- Ensure `CORS_ALLOW_CREDENTIALS = True` for cookie support.
- Add `dj_rest_auth.jwt_auth.JWTCookieAuthentication` to `REST_FRAMEWORK['DEFAULT_AUTHENTICATION_CLASSES']`.
- Update SimpleJWT settings for cookie paths and refresh token logic.

